description: Outline planning application showing layout, scale and access for the phased demolition and phased redevelopment of the Packington Estate allowing for the erection of part 1 to 8 storey buildings (some with basement level) to provide for: 538 (264x1, 134x2, 95x3, 28x4, 14x5 and 3x6 bedroom) affordable housing flats/maisonettes/houses (1695 habitable rooms), 301 (181x1 and 120x2 bedroom) market-housing flats for private sale (722 habitable rooms), 800sqm of retail floorspace (A1 use), 290sqm community centre (D1 use) and an outdoor recreation facility of no less than 446sqm.  Erection of a 3-storey 300sqm workshop (B1 use) and single storey 200sqm youth centre (D1 use).  Provision of an adventure playground of no less than 997sqm in area, open space (hard and soft landscaped and play areas) of no less than 8778sqm, semi-private open space of no less than 540sqm and private gardens of no less than 12,448sqm;  Creation of new roads and a cycle path, no more than 270 car parking spaces and no less than 420 bicycle spaces.  Erection of a Combined Heat and Power / biomass energy facility and green/brown roofs covering an area no less than 1372sqm. (DEPARTURE FROM PLAN owing to the loss of 2442sqm of open space).
decision_conditions:
The application for the approval of reserved matters must be made to the Local Planning Authority no later than the expiry of three (3) years beginning with the date of this outline planning consent and the development to which the permission relates must be begun no later than the expiration of two (2) years from the final approval of the reserved matters, or in the case of approval on different dates, the final approval of the last such matter approved. 

REASON: To comply with Section 92(2) of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990 as amended by Section 51(2) of the Planning Compulsory Purchase Act 2004.
